      <hedline>
        <hl1>Is Retirement a Gift or a Burden?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Perry Greenberg on William Safire's June 26 Op-Ed column on Social Security</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>William Safire says we should work past the age of 65 lest the mind atrophy as we go off fishing (column, June 26). The assumption is that we're all working on the human genome project. For most of us, though, our 9-to-5 jobs are mind-numbing and don't require the creativity and mental resourcefulness of battling a cunning trout.</p>
        <p>PERRY GREENBERG  New York, June 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
